{"id":9713,"date":"2024-01-23T18:25:25","date_gmt":"2020-05-23T12:55:25","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=9713"},"modified":"2023-06-19T11:28:42","modified_gmt":"2023-06-19T05:58:42","slug":"under-sink-storage-ideas","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/under-sink-storage-ideas\/","title":{"rendered":"Under Sink Storage Ideas For Bathrooms And Kitchens"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><em>Difficulty finding storage in your bathroom and kitchen? Declutter this troubled spot with these handy design hacks&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>When it comes to the kitchens and bathrooms, storage is key. Not all of us in our urban Indian homes enjoy a spacious, luxurious bathroom as one sees in interior design magazines. But that should not stop you from living well. The key to the good bathroom and kitchen interior design is smart and innovative storage solutions which makes organisation and cleaning a piece of cake. One smart way to maximise kitchen and bathroom storage is by utilising the area under the sink.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We often designate the area under the sink as a dumping ground. Tossing and shoving things without much thought. And when it comes to finding a particular item, it becomes an impossible task. We\u2019re sure you can relate to the problems we face every day. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/\">DesignCafe<\/a> is here to solve just that. These ideas will transform even the tiniest space in your kitchen or bathroom into an organised and clutter-free haven.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">A Vanity Unit For Bathroom Storage<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you are looking for adequate storage for your bathroom, nothing beats a bathroom vanity unit with cabinets under the sink. A unit such as this in the image here will help you store cleaning supplies, bathing products, in a neat and hidden manner. You can purchase these units from stores, or you can custom build your own with the help of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/\">interior design professionals<\/a>. This is a neat way to keep your bathroom clutter-free and find much-needed products anytime you want.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181744\/under-bathroom-sink-storage-vanity-unit.jpg\" alt=\"Bathroom vanity unit with cabinets under sink storage will help you store cleaning, bathing products, neatly &amp; hidden manner.\" class=\"wp-image-9718\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181744\/under-bathroom-sink-storage-vanity-unit.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181744\/under-bathroom-sink-storage-vanity-unit-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181744\/under-bathroom-sink-storage-vanity-unit-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181744\/under-bathroom-sink-storage-vanity-unit-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Make sure the material is waterproof and the unit is built away from the shower<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, check out <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bathroom-interiors\/bathroom-storage-ideas\/\">Creative Bathroom Storage Ideas<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Cupboards And Drawers Under The Sink<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Nothing is more irritating than struggling to find items in cramped cabinets. We all know how our bathrooms tend to get quickly cluttered with both essential and non-essential items. If your bathroom is deprived of storage because it is small then why not build drawers and cabinets under your sink? This will solve all your woes as you can store your toiletries, towels and other items in these drawers and cabinets and access them whenever needed.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181518\/cupboards-drawers-under-bathroom-sink-storage.jpg\" alt=\"White cabinet &amp; drawer under bathroom sink storage can store both essential and non-essential items with clutter-free.\" class=\"wp-image-9715\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181518\/cupboards-drawers-under-bathroom-sink-storage.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181518\/cupboards-drawers-under-bathroom-sink-storage-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181518\/cupboards-drawers-under-bathroom-sink-storage-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181518\/cupboards-drawers-under-bathroom-sink-storage-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"End to end interior solutions that save 20% extra space\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/06\/19103933\/end-to-end-interior-solutions-that-save-20-extra-space.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, check out\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bathroom-interiors\/bathroom-cabinet-designs\/\">Bathroom Cabinets \u2013 Check Mirror\u00a0 Cabinet, Corner Cabinet<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Open Shelves Under The Bathroom Sink<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Open shelves are an excellent way to turn your everyday products into decor items and keep the space clean. Plus, they are great to store extra towels and other large items that otherwise end up in a closet. A mix of drawers and open shelves with wicker baskets (<em>to store small essentials like makeup and toiletries<\/em>) while the open shelves can house towels and clothing.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181611\/open-shelves-under-bathroom-sink-storage-ideas.jpg\" alt=\"Under bathroom sink storage ideas open shelves with wicker baskets help to store essential items and keep the space clean.\" class=\"wp-image-9716\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181611\/open-shelves-under-bathroom-sink-storage-ideas.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181611\/open-shelves-under-bathroom-sink-storage-ideas-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181611\/open-shelves-under-bathroom-sink-storage-ideas-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181611\/open-shelves-under-bathroom-sink-storage-ideas-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>If you have free space below the sink it&#8217;s a great idea to use a basket to keep unwanted items of clothing<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">A Deep Drawer Organiser<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The easiest way to get the most out of your sink and free space is to build a deep drawer. A deep drawer allows you to store long utensils that are not limited to your normal cutlery. Here you can store pots, pans and large boxes of Tupperware. This organisation hack will let you save time searching for large utensils when you are in the midst of cooking. These deep drawer organisers will help you keep your kitchen clean and you will feel far more efficient.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181835\/under-kitchen-sink-cabinet-storage-ideas.jpg\" alt=\"Under kitchen sink pull out storage helps to store items from kitchen microfiber towels to empty pots and pans.\" class=\"wp-image-9719\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181835\/under-kitchen-sink-cabinet-storage-ideas.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181835\/under-kitchen-sink-cabinet-storage-ideas-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181835\/under-kitchen-sink-cabinet-storage-ideas-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181835\/under-kitchen-sink-cabinet-storage-ideas-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A pull-out organizer can help store items with ease from empty jars to pots and pans<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, check out <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/different-types-of-kitchen-sink-designs\/\">Different Types of Kitchen Sink Designs in India<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Recycle and Organise Kitchen Trash<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Adual dustbin to segregate wet and dry trash is a smart organisation hack. It is ideal to design this under the sink where it is at easy reach. This keeps the bin and its contents out of sight. The reason why trash bins are kept just under the sink or next to it is that it needs to be close to where much of the food preparations are done. This will make it convenient for you to wipe food remnants off the counter and into the bin.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181659\/organize-kitchen-trash-under-sink-storage.jpg\" alt=\"Under kitchen sink cabinet storage ideas dual dustbin to segregate wet and dry trash is a smart organisation hack.\" class=\"wp-image-9717\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181659\/organize-kitchen-trash-under-sink-storage.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181659\/organize-kitchen-trash-under-sink-storage-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181659\/organize-kitchen-trash-under-sink-storage-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181659\/organize-kitchen-trash-under-sink-storage-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>You can place garbage bags on the hook of the dustbin for easy access<br><\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Organise Kitchen Cleaners<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Keep your kitchen cleaning supplies, scrubbers, in an easy-to-pull out caddy or baskets as shown in this image here. This method for organisation lets you pull it out when it&#8217;s time to give everything a nice clean. If the space is wide enough, gear it with two, three-tier shelves with rolling drawers. Store disinfectants, scrubs, and sanitisers in one place with this caddy. You can even place a trash bin if you have space or make space for toilet paper rolls too.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181924\/under-sink-storage-cabinet-organiser.jpg\" alt=\"Under sink counter storage in the kitchen keep cleaning supplies, scrubbers, in an easy-to-pull out caddy for clutter-free.\" class=\"wp-image-9720\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181924\/under-sink-storage-cabinet-organiser.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181924\/under-sink-storage-cabinet-organiser-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181924\/under-sink-storage-cabinet-organiser-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/05\/23181924\/under-sink-storage-cabinet-organiser-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>You can also use a tension rod for your shower sprays, glass cleaners to hang them separately<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a Free Modular Kitchen Worth \u20b92 Lakhs with Your Home Interiors.\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/08183703\/designcafe-offer-free-modular-kitchen-worth-2-lakhs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>We all know the pain of not having enough storage space in bathrooms and kitchens. With simple remodelling and smart design hacks, you can create an ample amount of space under the sink.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Explore, More About<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/5-ideas-to-enhance-kitchen-organization\/\">5 Genius Ideas to Enhance Kitchen Organisation<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/kitchen-organisation-ideas\/\">10 Kitchen Organisation Ideas For Your Home<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bathroom-interiors\/bathroom-sink-design-ideas\/\">Bathroom Sink Design Ideas For Your Home<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Looking For Functional Interior Designs?<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Get 20% extra space with smart solutions<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span class=\"sal